This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as question answering and text classification, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained language encoders such as BERT, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions regression tasks, which can be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. However, since the focus of the paper is on natural language processing tasks, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI.
